==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unbishop
<hw>Un*bish"op</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>bishop</ets>.]</ety> <def>To deprive, as a city,
of a bishop; to deprive, as a clergyman, of episcopal dignity or
rights.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Then he <xex>unbishops</xex>
himself.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unbit</ent>⟦br⟧
